Cleansing Fire Plugin Directory

Plugins are executable scripts that:
1. Accept JSON input on stdin
2. Produce JSON output on stdout
3. Return exit code 0 on success, non-zero on failure
4. Have access to CF_PROJECT_DIR environment variable

Plugin naming convention: <category>-<name>
  e.g., civic-foia-generator, osint-corporate-lookup, media-fediverse-post

Plugins can call the Gatekeeper for LLM tasks:
  curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:7800/submit-sync \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d '{"prompt": "...", "caller": "plugin:<name>"}'
